                               Description
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Is becoming a woman analogous, in some deep psychological way, to becoming
a werewolf? Ginger is 16, edgy, tough, and, with her younger sister, into
staging and photographing scenes of death. They&#039;ve made a pact about dying
together. In early October, on the night she has her first period, which
is also the night of a full moon, a werewolf bites Ginger. Within a few
days, some serious changes happen to her body and her temperament. Her
sister Brigitte, 15, tries to find a cure with the help of Sam, a local
doper. As Brigitte races against the clock, Halloween and another full
moon approach, Ginger gets scarier, and it isn&#039;t just local dogs that
begin to die.
